OTHER THINGS POINTED OUT

Why can’t you do this in a desert?
This question was asked in regard to my statements about finding a spot to put the sea of cheese graters. Many have said that I should instead place the sea in a desert because that wouldn’t be littering. Unfortunately, the closest deserts, namely in the middle of Australia and Antarctica, fall in Australian and International Waters territory, of which littering is banned. The next closest, likely the Gobi, is in China/Mongolia and this is also banned under recorded legislation. Therefore, it’s much more cost effective to do this in a hired space rather than fly to another country, as well as the fact that it saves time.
